The paper deals with lower bounds on automata and communication complexity, which are topics typically studied in computer science theory. Specifically, the paper focuses on the problem of Parity Games, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of communication complexity techniques also suggests a possible categorization under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.LO (logic in computer science). Additionally, the paper discusses automata and their states, which could fall under cs.CG (computational geometry) or cs.GT (computer science and game theory).
